line_2: " Virtue and Vice are merely names,
Since thy false heart a spouse divine disclaims,
I leave thee to the pomp which here thy pride enflames. "

line_1: "Fly from these dangerous walls," his page exclaims;
line_2: See thy knight's wondrous dart in terror flames;

line_1: "Ay, may be so," Lord RICH exclaims,
Ye groves (the statesman at his desk exclaims
line_2: Sick of a thousand disappointed aims)
